        <body>       

                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>THE MENORAH MONTHLY&#44;<lb/>
                <emph rend="italics">Editorial Rooms&#58;</emph><lb/>
                39 BROADWAY&#44;<lb/>
                NEW YORK.<lb/></p>
            <p>New York&#44; Sept 10 1889<lb/></p>
            <p>Esteemed &#38; Rev friend.<lb/></p>
            <p>Your 2<hi rend="sup">d</hi> &#38; 3<hi rend="sup">d</hi> series<lb/> were duly recd and will appear<lb/> in the order named&#58;<lb/> <hi rend="underline">Sept</hi>&#44; Menorah&#59; <hi rend="underline">Massarin Asedli&#91;&#63;&#93;</hi><lb/> &#38; David Levi<lb/></p>
            <p><hi rend="underline">Oct</hi>&#44; Menorah. Luzzatti&#44; Franeletti<lb/> &#38; Arbib<lb/></p>
            <p>Proofs of the Spet no will be<lb/> sent you by Mr Cowen with <hi rend="underline">MS</hi><lb/> so that you can retain latter<lb/> each time.<lb/></p>
            <p>The loss of a dear<lb/> sister&#44; the critical illness of my<lb/> brother &#38; my own indisposition<lb/> have quite unfitted me for<lb/> any thing recently but I<lb/> am rapidly getting in order<lb/> now &#38; if no relapses take place<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>hope all will go well.<lb/></p>
            <p>I have been also<lb/> greatly troubled in perfecting<lb/> the organization of the Menorah<lb/> Co&#44; this task has been one of<lb/> most trying and harassing<lb/> I have ever known.  The pitiful&#45;<lb/>ness of man&#39;s character and<lb/> especially of Jewish character<lb/> I have rarely ever seen so<lb/> wretchedly unfolded.<lb/></p>
            <p>D. V. I shall yet<lb/> pull through&#45;&#45;only my heart is<lb/> very sick.<lb/></p>
            <p>I cannot express to you<lb/> Rev friend how greatly I appreciate<lb/> your valuable and beautiful<lb/> collaborations&#44; These Historical<lb/> outlines will become memorable<lb/> Sincerely Yr friend<lb/> Ben F. Peixotto<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev Dr. S. Morais<lb/> Phila<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
